    "display_name": "School Shop",
    "long_instructions": "## **Do This**\r\n\r\n<br/> 1. **Choose a key user task.**\r\nThink about something a visitor might do on a pet adoption web app, such as:\r\n\r\n* Browse pets by type or age\r\n* Learn about the adoption process\r\n* Contact the shelter for more information\r\n\r\n<br/> 2. **Trace the path.**\r\nOn your site map, show the pages a user would move through to complete that task.\r\n\r\n* Use **arrows or labels** to mark each click or page change.\r\n* Or write out the steps as a short list (e.g., *Home → Pets → Dog Profiles → Adoption Info*).\r\n\r\n<br/> 3. **Peer-test it.**\r\nPair up with another student:\r\n\r\n* One person plays the **user**, describing what they'd click.\r\n* The other follows along on the site map.\r\n* Notice where the user gets lost or repeats steps.\r\n\r\n",
    "bubble_choice_description": "Use your site map to explore how people interact with a pet adoption web app.",
